OL,3,CKhalife guilty of spying for Iran: How
OL,4,Cteen turned into 'slapstick' James Bond
OL,6,FIn September 2023, he broke out of the
OL,7,FSouth London prison by tying himself
OL,8,Funder a lorry using a sling from his
OL,9,Fkitchen trousers.
OL,11,FHis escape launched one of the biggest
OL,12,Fmanhunts in recent years. He gained
OL,13,Fnational attention after being spotted
OL,14,Fbuying clothes from Marks & Spencer
OL,15,Fand a coffee from McDonald's in
OL,16,FRichmond as well as reading newspaper
OL,17,Farticles about himself.
OL,19,FHe was caught on CCTV strolling beside
OL,20,Fthe River Thames before being caught
OL,21,Fby police three days later.
